The article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Donald Trump on February 12, 2018. The memorandum relates to the sequestration order for fiscal year 2019, in accordance with section 251A of the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act. The order states that on October 1, 2018, direct spending budgetary resources for fiscal year 2019 in each non-exempt budget account should be reduced by the amount calculated by the Office of Management and Budget. The order emphasizes that all sequestrations should be made in strict accordance with the requirements of section 251A and the specifications of the Office of Management and Budget's report.